This paper deals with a communication channel model that includes noise and filtering effects, which are typical topics in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of a receiver in terms of rate and pre-log factor, which are related to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a channel model that takes into account the effect of filtering on the phase noise, which is a topic in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
